  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/32774458?book_show_action=true">Sep 13, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="LJ" class="user" itemprop="url" name="LJ" href="/user/show/250195-lj">LJ</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780399133497" href="/book/show/77065.Hot_Money">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/250195-lj?shelf=action_suspense">action_suspense</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/250195-lj?shelf=male_author">male_author</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/250195-lj?shelf=dick_francis">dick_francis</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/250195-lj?shelf=contemporary_post_1945">contemporary_post_1945</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/250195-lj?shelf=amateur_sleuth">amateur_sleuth</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/250195-lj?shelf=england">england</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer32774458" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5952010663571624283">HOT MONEY - Ex<br/>Francis, Dick - 26th book<br/><br/>With his five ex-wives and the nine children between them, it&apos;s no great surprise that spectacularly wealthy gold trader Malcolm Pembroke should preside over a motley clan in constant conflict with one another.<br/><br/>But when violent death strikes the least likable of his former spouses, Malcolm himself feels threatened, and he calls on his most capable son, Ian, the family jockey. Ian&apos;s task: to protect his father from their nearest, if not always dearest, relati</span>
  <span id="freeText5952010663571624283" style="display:none">HOT MONEY - Ex<br />Francis, Dick - 26th book<br /><br />With his five ex-wives and the nine children between them, it's no great surprise that spectacularly wealthy gold trader Malcolm Pembroke should preside over a motley clan in constant conflict with one another.<br /><br />But when violent death strikes the least likable of his former spouses, Malcolm himself feels threatened, and he calls on his most capable son, Ian, the family jockey. Ian's task: to protect his father from their nearest, if not always dearest, relatives—and to delve for the final, critical clue in the darkly buried Pembroke past, simmering with the greed, hate, and vengefulness that could motivate blood to strike against blood.<br /><br />This is another of my favorites. Great protagonist and I loved the relationship between him and his father.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5952010663571624283" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


