<div id="review_162636552" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/162636552" />
    <a title="Sheila Beaumont" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3303083-sheila-beaumont"><img alt="Sheila Beaumont" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1266970607p2/3303083.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/162636552?book_show_action=true">Apr 21, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sheila Beaumont" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sheila Beaumont" href="/user/show/3303083-sheila-beaumont">Sheila Beaumont</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780425235409" href="/book/show/7936039-hot-money">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3303083-sheila-beaumont?shelf=action-and-adventure">action-and-adventure</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3303083-sheila-beaumont?shelf=adult-fiction">adult-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3303083-sheila-beaumont?shelf=mysteries-suspense-thrillers">mysteries-suspense-thrillers</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer162636552" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15285546930510228229">I loved this book! I&apos;ve enjoyed all of Dick Francis&apos; mysteries that I&apos;ve read so far, and this is my favorite of them. As always, there&apos;s a likable protagonist, and I also liked his lively multimillionaire father, who, apparently endangered by someone in his large extended family, calls upon his most trusted son, an amateur jockey, to protect him. Perfect pacing, shocking twists, good writing, quite a few comical scenes, and detailed portrayals of the various greedy, spiteful, squabbling family </span>
  <span id="freeText15285546930510228229" style="display:none">I loved this book! I've enjoyed all of Dick Francis' mysteries that I've read so far, and this is my favorite of them. As always, there's a likable protagonist, and I also liked his lively multimillionaire father, who, apparently endangered by someone in his large extended family, calls upon his most trusted son, an amateur jockey, to protect him. Perfect pacing, shocking twists, good writing, quite a few comical scenes, and detailed portrayals of the various greedy, spiteful, squabbling family members make for a spellbinding tale. There are still a lot of Francis' mysteries I haven't read yet, and I'm eagerly looking forward to them.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15285546930510228229" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


