<div id="review_1094639880" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1094639880" />
    <a title="Kati" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/198122-kati"><img alt="Kati" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1625749050p2/198122.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1094639880?book_show_action=true">Nov 01, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kati" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kati" href="/user/show/198122-kati">Kati</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780718140953" href="/book/show/8567.Hot_Money">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/198122-kati?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/198122-kati?shelf=in-czech">in-czech</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/198122-kati?shelf=2014">2014</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1094639880" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer544561442779861748">More of a character study than a mystery, a study of a large, dysfunctional family on the brink of a collapse. And my favorite Dick Francis novel, hands down. Ian Pembroke is my favorite Francis hero, nothing seems to faze the guy, and I loved his relationship with his father, Malcolm. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


